abstract: Dozens of Cubans gather outside Ecuadorean embassy in Havana to complain about implementation of visa requirement for Cubans; Ecuador is only Latin American country that did not require visa for  Cubans who wanted to enter country, and had thus become stepping-stone for Cubans who wished to then make it to United States.
lead_paragraph: Cubans crowded outside an Ecuadorean embassy, worried about a new visa requirement to enter Ecuador, a vital step to reach the United States.

headline.main: Cubans Protest Stricter Rules for Traveling to Ecuador
headline.print_headline: Cubans Protest Stricter Rules for Traveling to Ecuador
